IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. SIMPLE-EDITOR.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.
* Hear ye, hear ye! This humble program doth serve as a simple text editor,
* a tool for the noble programmers to practice their craft. With this, they
* shall learn to wield the power of COBOL, to edit and save text with grace
* and precision. Let the journey begin!

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
CONFIGURATION SECTION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'INPUT.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(80).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(80).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-EOF PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  WS-TEMP PIC X(80).
01  WS-RAIN PIC X(80).
01  WS-SUNSHINE PIC X(80).
01  WS-FOG PIC X(80).
01  WS-THUNDER PIC X(80).
01  WS-INPUT-LINE PIC X(80).
01  WS-OUTPUT-LINE PIC X(80).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PARA.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE
    PERFORM UNTIL WS-EOF = 'Y'
     READ INPUT-FILE INTO WS-INPUT-LINE
         AT END
          MOVE 'Y' TO WS-EOF
         NOT AT END
          MOVE WS-INPUT-LINE TO WS-OUTPUT-LINE
          PERFORM WRITE-OUTPUT
     END-READ
    END-PERFORM
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE
    STOP RUN.

WRITE-OUTPUT.
    MOVE WS-OUTPUT-LINE TO OUTPUT-RECORD
    WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD.

